===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|則|戈|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|t2=weapon}}.

This was later reinterpreted as a compound of {{zh-l|*貝|money}} and {{zh-l|*戎|weapon}} to produce the modern form.

===Etymology 1===
Possibly {{der|zh|sit}}; compare {{cog|bo|ཇག||robbery}} ({{zh-ref|Coblin, 1986}}). {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} points out that a palatalized consonant in {{cog|bo|-}} does not usually correspond to an unpalatalized one in Chinese; instead, he compares it to {{cog|km|ឆក់||to snatch; to steal}}.

Possibly cognate with {{och-l|災|natural disaster}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Based on evidence from early loans from Chinese, e.g. {{cog|lbc|kjak⁸||bandit}} and {{w|Chut language|Rục}} {{m|scb|kəcʌ́ːk||bandit}}, {{zh-ref|Baxter and Sagart (2014)}} reconstructs the Old Chinese with a ''*k'' preinitial.

